13
00:53:23.025 --> 00:53:38.294
Incoming livestream: So, of course, it's not just the speed of errors, because, yes, it's all the force and the motion and the physics of the errors, but there's also timing, because you need to detect these errors in time before the action takes place.

14
00:53:38.885 --> 00:53:46.434
Incoming livestream: Of course, as you know, that in the physical AI space, the errors are not very reversible.

15
00:53:52.385 --> 00:54:00.244
Incoming livestream: So the reason, this is of importance right now is 3 different kinds of technologies have crossed over.

16
00:54:00.515 --> 00:54:20.184
Incoming livestream: We have sensors, and sensors have matured a lot. And of course, foundational models, frontier models, have become very stable, less of hallucinations, and the last part of it is edge compute. Edge compute is much more viable and feasible today. Now, these three vectors together have made the need

17
00:54:20.325 --> 00:54:23.134
Incoming livestream: Increase the need for autonomous economy.

18
00:54:25.725 --> 00:54:32.914
Incoming livestream: Let's talk about the building blocks of physical AI. Basically, think of it as a loop. You have sensors in the field.

19
00:54:33.355 --> 00:54:45.815
Incoming livestream: Then, you have technology that detects the sensor… information from the sensors. Then you have something called the perception layer, which is basically making sense of the sensor's data.

20
00:54:46.635 --> 00:54:57.515
Incoming livestream: And then you have the thinking. Thinking is basically trying to map the data, the state of the world, and the sensor data, and trying to figure… predict the next

21
00:54:57.745 --> 00:54:59.375
Incoming livestream: State of the system.

22
00:55:00.315 --> 00:55:12.135
Incoming livestream: And of course, you have reasoning and planning, what do I do? What… if I take this action, what is going to happen? And finally, it is more about controlling and actually driving the physical actions.

23
00:55:14.875 --> 00:55:19.165
Incoming livestream: So, it's not a new concept. Physical AI was there.

24
00:55:19.395 --> 00:55:25.544
Incoming livestream: Except that none of the technologies had matured enough for them to be deployed at scale in the field.

25
00:55:26.395 --> 00:55:43.815
Incoming livestream: Okay? So in the 1950s and 2000… up to 2000, we had a lot of world models, which are basically control theory, robotics, etc, and they were able to look at the state and predict the next state of the system, so they could say that if I take this action, what is… what'll happen to the world?

26
00:55:44.775 --> 00:55:48.295
Incoming livestream: Then, of course, came the LLMs, which are the brains, right?

27
00:55:48.765 --> 00:55:54.534
Incoming livestream: the brains work, given what I see, what is a text, what action should I take?

28
00:55:55.565 --> 00:56:05.155
Incoming livestream: what should be my response? And the next one is VLMs, the visual language models. If I… given what the text I see and the images I see.

29
00:56:05.545 --> 00:56:16.635
Incoming livestream: what does this mean to me? What does this mean in the physical world? And finally, the vision language action models, which basically is saying, okay, given the perception, given the state of the world.

30
00:56:17.155 --> 00:56:27.084
Incoming livestream: And what action should I take? That means, what do I tell the physical system, which is the robot? How much do I move, the arm of the robot, or the legs of the robot, etc.

31
00:56:27.225 --> 00:56:35.824
Incoming livestream: So these three… all these come into play. Now, remember our, loop that we were talking about? The five layers? Now let's see how they map.

32
00:56:35.975 --> 00:56:44.525
Incoming livestream: You have the sensors, you have the perceivers, right? Sensors are the standard sensors, the LiDARs, etc. The thinking is the world model.

33
00:56:45.045 --> 00:56:54.585
Incoming livestream: And then the reasoning and the planning are the LLMs and the VLMs, and of course, the control and action are the actual robotic movements.

34
00:56:59.245 --> 00:57:03.794
Incoming livestream: So now we'll go through a step where I'll take you through this physical stack.

35
00:57:03.995 --> 00:57:09.634
